In 0.10.10-insider the following code causes the "Go to symbol..."-box to state "No symbols found".

`(function() {
    function foo() { }
})();`

I would expect to see 'foo' listed as a symbol, which is the case without the IIFE.

When contributing a language, it is possible to specify `filenamePatterns`.

The property gets lost and not used in determining the language when opening a file.

```

  "contributes": {
      "languages": [
          {
              "id": "dockerfile",
              "aliases": [
                  "Dockerfile"
              ],
              "filenamePatterns": [
                  "dockerfile.*",
                  "Dockerfile*.*"
              ]
          }
      ],

```
